reviews.text:
Strangest Mexican food I've had. The food itself was well made and tasted good but there were some interesting choices. One of the side sauces was ranch? and there was no pico de gallo? There was probably a bit too much cheese (I think I used maybe half, really trying to use it) and just some side lettuce (no tomato or pico as mentioned).
Overall the food was good but very different from what I normally would expect.

Good restaurant for a small group of people. I was surprised how squeezed we were at our table, I could barely hold my knife without hitting my colleague. At the end of the day we had lots of fun, the decoration is original and really nice.

I was not really impressed with the dessert menu , so if you are going there for mostly dessert you will probably be disappointed.

Food was good and service was Ok, nothing really special.

just look at these tacos and tell me would you ever order them again?
they taste as bland as they look, like tap water with a sprinkle of salt.

I can't belive I spent 15 euros for this heartless meal when there are much better options of food in Zagreb.
